The proposed workaround of deriving POTENTIAL_EARLIEST_TRNSCTN_DT = EFCTV_DTS - 30 days is not reliable, as EFCTV_DTS itself is inconsistent across transaction types. In several cases, particularly for MTA records, the effective date incorrectly retains the original New Business effective date instead of reflecting the actual adjustment timing. This indicates a source data quality issue where effective dates are reused or not updated correctly. As a result, using EFCTV_DTS as a fallback would propagate the same inaccuracies and lead to incorrect retention decisions.
